Currently we can show Business information when hovering a username by adding {{show.business.group.in.user.hover}} in {{<URL>/admin/darkfeatures.action}}.

The script responsible for the _hover_ function is the {{<confluence-install>/confluence/includes/js/components/binders/hover-user.js}}, which creates a call for this URL when the dark feature is enabled: {{<URL>/users/userinfopopup.action?username=username123&profileGroups=business}}

If we use this URL for the *admin* user, which has business information, this is the result we get:
!businessAdminInfo.png|thumbnail!

It's possible to add _personal_ to this URL {{<URL>/users/userinfopopup.action?username=admin&profileGroups=business,personal}}, which would then return the phone number too:
!businessPersonalAdminInfo.png|thumbnail!

It would be awesome to add this option in the dark feature too, since the resolution seems to be simple.

